cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.CG 

The paper deals with extracting surfaces from 3D images, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of the Fast Marching algorithm and the framework of cubical complexes and Morse theory suggests that the paper may also be relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA), data structures (cs.DS), and computational geometry (cs.CG).
